{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8b28070b-9b65-46a2-a5ab-8b69df5dcbc8","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) that need version bumps to their .NET 11-compatible releases.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b50f26c3-2246-4f0a-bdd5-dec5f6bf6648","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":283,"requestId":"E037:18DC0C:71C93C9:7E91C61:69F406ED"},"id":"9ff415b9-25bd-4d2f-a55a-65c32a9b7cbc","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:50:43.906Z","parentId":"2d15ceb4-42a1-436b-840f-9de11bb17f8b"}
